summary: The document is a declassified routing and record sheet from 1973, detailing the transfer of alias documents such as CIA credentials, driver's licenses, social security cards, and other identification cards under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992. It was addressed to WH/Security from the Foreign Resources Division and is marked with classifications including SECRET and CONFIDENTIAL, highlighting its sensitive nature and providing insight into the administrative and security processes of the time.
key_findings: The document is part of the records released under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
It details the transfer of alias documents including CIA credentials and various forms of identification.
The document is marked with security classifications indicating its sensitive nature at the time.
Dated August 15, 1973, it provides insight into the administrative processes of the time regarding document handling and security.
